text: The common coquí or coquí (Eleutherodactylus coqui) is a species of frog. They live in Puerto Rico. The coquí is an important symbol of Puerto Rico. They are known for their loud calls they make at night. They belong to the genus Eleutherodactylus. ==References== ==Books== * ==Other websites== * Control of Coqui Frog in Hawaii * Eleutherodactylus coqui information from HEAR * Children Story About Coqui; El Coqui De Madagascar Category:Frogs of North America Category:Puerto Rico
